We don't want the factory constructors to be used, since only a user can authenticate to manage projects, so this note should be squashed. You may even want to consider overwriting the methods from the superclass:

```python
    @classmethod
    def from_service_account_json(cls, *args, **kwargs):
        raise NotImplementedError(args, kwargs)

    @classmethod
    def from_service_account_p12(cls, *args, **kwargs):
        raise NotImplementedError(args, kwargs)
```

Totally a personal preference thing, but I dislike `switch` statements because of the `break`s, `default`, and weird indentation rules. Reminds me of coding in assembly :)

One alternative:

```javascript
handleKeyboardNav(e) {
  if (this.showDropdown && this.suggestions.length) {
    if (e.code === 'Enter') {
      this.fillUsername(this.suggestions[this.highlightedIndex]);
      e.preventDefault();
    } else if (e.code === 'Escape') {
      this.showDropdown = false;
    } else if (e.code === 'ArrowDown') {
      this.highlightedIndex = Math.min(this.highlightedIndex + 1, this.suggestions.length - 1);
    } else if (e.code === 'ArrowUp') {
      this.highlightedIndex = Math.max(this.highlightedIndex - 1, -1);
    }
  }
},
```

